  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legal definitions typically include:\n\n1. Concealing the origin of criminally-derived funds\n2. Disguising the true source of money obtained through illegal activities\n3. Transforming \"dirty\" money into seemingly legitimate financial assets\n4. Transferring funds to hide their illegal source\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve three key stages:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial systems)\n- Layering (concealing the source through complex transactions)\n- Integration (reintroducing funds into legitimate economy)\n\nMost jurisdictions consider money laundering a criminal offense with potential penalties including:\n- Financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Imprisonment\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
